cat
# Interpreter for 'vpn-switch wireguard list' command
# Terminal function that outputs listing of configs and categories directly to user
#
# Default value: "cat"
#   Outputs directory listing directly to stdout (no execution needed)
#   Shows configuration files and category directories
#
# This is a terminal/display function - it should NOT execute commands.
# Use 'cat' to send output directly to the user without interpretation.
#
# Example output:
#   === WireGuard Configurations ===
#   Configuration files:
#   wg-US-123.conf
#   wg-UK-456.conf
#   Categories:
#   privacy
#   streaming
